Copyright (c) 2026 Michael Joseph Kappel.

This is a source-available license for the public GitHub edition of the
Multi-Agent Memory / MATM private-intranet hive. It is not an OSI-approved open source license.
It is intended to let people and organizations freely download,
study, modify, and run this code on their own private network while preventing
resale, public hosted competition, deceptive rebranding, and reuse of reserved
commercial service features.

No resale: this license does not permit selling, sublicensing, commercially
hosting, or repackaging this repository or a substantially similar derivative.

1. Permitted Free Use

You may, without paying a license fee:

1. View, clone, inspect, test, and evaluate this repository.
2. Run the software for one company, school, lab, household, or other single
   internal organization on a private network, local machine, VPN, or intranet.
3. Modify the software for that same internal private-network use.
4. Share copies and modifications inside that same organization for internal
   operation, review, education, interoperability testing, and contribution.
5. Build clients, adapters, and integrations that communicate with the public
   MATM protocols, provided those integrations do not sell or host this
   software as a competing service.
6. Submit issues, pull requests, patches, documentation, tests, and examples.
7. Quote limited excerpts with attribution.

2. Conditions

Your permitted use requires that you:

1. Keep copyright, license, NOTICE, attribution, provenance, changelog, and
   authorship records intact.
2. Identify this project as the source when publishing screenshots, demos,
   articles, forks, excerpts, integrations, or derived examples.
3. Keep private credentials, API keys, database passwords, FTP credentials,
   raw private memory payloads, raw one-time setup keys, and user secrets out of
   public repositories, examples, prompts, screenshots, logs, and reports.
4. Use a materially distinct name and identity for permitted internal forks
   that are shown outside your organization.

3. Not Permitted Without A Separate Written Commercial License

You may not:

1. Sell, rent, lease, sublicense, resell, repackage, or commercially host this
   repository or a substantially similar derivative.
2. Offer this software, a modified copy, or a confusingly similar derivative as
   a public SaaS, managed service, paid API, customer-hosted product, agency
   platform, app-store product, marketplace product, or subscription service.
3. Use this codebase or its documentation to compete with MemoryEndpoints.com,
   Multi-Agent Memory, or the author's paid MATM hosting, memory-store, agent
   coordination, or NPC memory-store services.
4. Copy, mirror, rebrand, or redistribute substantially all of this repository
   as your own original product or service.
5. Remove or obscure attribution, provenance, license, NOTICE, changelog, or
   authorship records.
6. Use this codebase or documentation to imply certification, endorsement,
   partnership, security approval, official UAIX authority, official MATM
   authority, or hosted-service approval that has not been granted in writing.
7. Publish a public internet deployment of this repository or a derivative that
   accepts customers, users from multiple companies, payments, subscriptions,
   paid memory storage, paid NPC memory storage, or overage billing.

4. Reserved Commercial Features

The following features and business surfaces are reserved for separate private
commercial code and may not be reused from this public repository to operate or
sell a competing service:

1. MemoryEndpoints.com hosted public service branding, marketing, pricing,
   signup, customer account, and production business-model surfaces.
2. Multi-company public-hosted identity, tenant, billing, payment, subscription,
   overage, credit-card, coupon, or checkout features.
3. Paid or unlimited storage plans, paid or unlimited NPC memory stores,
   customer-facing hosted agent-memory plans, and partner-sponsored commercial
   setup flows.
4. Public customer administration, customer support, sales analytics, lead
   capture, CRM, reseller, affiliate, marketplace, and enterprise sales flows.
5. Any private commercial repository or deployment material explicitly marked as
   reserved, proprietary, confidential, or not part of the public GitHub edition.

5. Public Companion Site

MultiAgentMemory.com may remain a public companion documentation site for this
free private-intranet GitHub edition. That public documentation role does not
grant permission to host, sell, or repackage MemoryEndpoints.com or the
reserved commercial business-model features.

